name: CrossFit Cheltenham
about: CrossFit Cheltenham is Cheltenham's premier strength and conditioning facility.
description:
CrossFit Cheltenham is Cheltenham's premier strength and conditioning facility. At CrossFit Cheltenham you will follow a functional training program that will prepare you for anything life throws at you. Our training is constantly varied and performed at a high intensity so you get a great workout and never become bored as the sessions are always different. 

Due to the nature of the programming and scaling options we meet the needs of each and every individual that trains with us. So if you are an elite sports person competing at top level, or a Great Grandparent playing with the kids at weekends CrossFit Cheltenham is for you!

events.name: The African Maternity Link WODathon
events.description:
The African Maternity Link 24 hour WODathon- We are aiming to do one WOD each hour on the hour from 12 midday on Saturday 2nd July through to the last WOD at 12 midday on Sunday 3rd July!

All abilities are welcome and encouraged to come along and train with us! If you want to join us, please comment on here which times you would like to do, so that we can arrange the schedule.

It will be a fun 24 hours, but for a serious cause, so we hope you can either come along or support us with donations.

ALL proceeds made will go to The African Maternity Link (a small charity aiming to reduce the maternal and neonatal mortality and morbidity rates in Sierra Leone though education and training). Midwives travel to Sierra Leone to facilitate training, observe practice and teach new skills, including obstetric emergencies and the use of life saving drugs. The charity is slowly but surely saving lives and needs help through funding to continue the good work. 

www.theafricanmaternitylink.co.uk

All friends and family are welcome. There will be a BBQ on the Saturday afternoon and the Sunday afternoon. All donations are very gratefully received, and of course if you want to bring along baked goods that we could sell to raise money that would also be amazing!!

We hope you can make it to this awesome event!!! x

events.name: REGIONALS IN MADRID!!!
events.description:
Regionals is an amazing event to go and watch. The last few yers we have travelled to Copenhagen to watch Will (and David in 2014) compete amongst the best athletes in Europe!!! 

This year... IT'S IN MADRID!!!

So we are hoping to get a group of us going over to watch/support! We need to get an idea of numbers and whether you would be keen to share a big house (hopefully with a pool :D)! We will start to look at deals and book ASAP so if you know you're keen, please click 'going' so that we know how many people are interested!

Will is hopefully going to get there as an individual again and David has teamed up with five other great athletes who are hoping to get there as a team, so it should be a great trip! Also, the best female CrossFitters come from the European region (including last years overall Games winner Katrin Davidsdottir) and it's pretty fun to watch them battle to get to the Games! x

events.name: PUDDING CLUB!!!
events.description:
As some of you know, me (Kylie) and Steve have discovered a 'Pudding Club' at the Three Ways House in Chipping Campden!! We went a couple of months ago and had a great time, so thought it would be good to do as a box as we know there are some people that love a good pudding!!!

We have spoken to the Restuarant and they have agreed to put on an extra night just for us. To do this, they need at least 40 people to attend, with a maximum of 70 people. So we are keen to get numbers and see if we can do it!

We have arranged a provisional date for the weekend after the Open (Sat 9th April) as we thought everyone could do with a treat! :D

What does it involve?
- Elderflower drink on arrival whilst the Pudding master goes through the puddings that evening
- A small main meal (when we went it was either Beef/Salmon and veg or risotto)
- After the dinner the waiters and waitresses parade the puddings so that you can see what is on offer. There will be a selection of 7 puddings. When we went there was butterscotch pudding, chocolate cake, spotted dick, plum crumble, passionfruit roulade, lemon drizzle, bread and butter pudding and they were all amazing!
- Then table number 1 is called up to collect their first pudding (which you can choose yourself) with whatever custard/extra sauce etc you might like
- The tables are then each called up in turn for their first round
- Then it goes on until there have been 7 rounds (so 7 puddings if you can manage it!)
- After the 7th round, the people that are still able to are given the opportunity to go up again (as many times as you like) and have a free for all!!!

If you love a sweet treat, this will be a good event for you!

I'm hoping we can get 40 people to come so that we can do it! Please only click 'going' if you are keen!!! xxx

¬£37.50 per person!

Check out the website here- http://www.threewayshousehotel.com/pudding_club/

events.name: Reebok CrossFit Games Open at CrossFit Cheltenham!!!
events.description:
Since 2011, the five-week five-workout online competition has accurately ranked the fitness of thousands of CrossFitters.

Held in CrossFit affiliates and garage gyms, the Open is designed to be accessible to all athletes while rigorous enough to challenge the world's fittest. Fourteen-year-old high school freshmen compete in the Open, as well as their 77-year-old grandparents and everyone in between.

Sign up for $20, do the workouts, enter your scores, and you will be ranked in relation to your peers in your age division, competition region, and country. 

Workouts are released online each Thursday and athletes have until the following Monday to submit their scores. 

It all starts February 25, 2016.

The Open brings the box together and there is such a buzzing atmosphere during this time! We will be hitting the workouts every Thursday in class and then over the weekend and during Monday nights competitors classes! Get involved gang!!! x

http://games.crossfit.com/about-the-games/the-open
